s and English alike, for his fairness and his piety. Edward's mother was Norman; he had spent part of his youth in Normandy; and William claimed to have been nominated by Edward as his successor. Edward was canonized in the 12th century, and came to be venerated throughout Europe as a model of a Christian king."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Ralf De Dol was born in 1155, in Lanherne, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Ralf de Dol."},"et":{"1155–":"1155–Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1155":"1155","1150":"1150","Abt 1180":"umbes 1180","1180":"1180","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lanherne, Cornwall, England":"Lanherne, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1155–":"1155–Kuollut","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1155":"1155","1150":"1150","Abt 1180":"noin 1180","1180":"1180","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lanherne, Cornwall, England":"Lanherne, Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1155–":"1155–Décédée","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","1180–Female":"1180–Décédée","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1155":"1155","1150":"1150","Abt 1180":"environ 1180","1180":"1180","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Lanherne, Cornwall, England":"Lanherne, Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Ralf De Dol est née en 1155, à Lanherne, Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Ralf de Dol."},"de":{"1155–":"1155–Verstorben","1150–Male":"1150–Verstorben","1180–Female":"1180–Verstorben","1155–Female":"1155–Verstorben","1155":"1155","1150":"1150","Abt 1180":"um 1180","1180":"1180","Devonshire, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Lanherne, Cornwall, England":"Lanherne, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Ralf De Dol wurde 1155 in Lanherne, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatt